715504f-b.title: Manhattan: 128th Street (West) - Convent Avenue
715504f-b.text:
WWest 128t Street, :est fror ConventAVenue. To the left
center is a space (details in views 2 and 3) where a boiler of
this brewery exploded and caused extensive damage recently.
G.WW. Hromley's atlas of 1922 ives the owner of same as the
Eernheimer and Schhwartz hilsener 'Brewing Company. Note the
cat walk connecting building units on opposite sides of the street.
April 1, 1938.
Views 1,2 and 3
